oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Grand Ole Opry - Prince Albert - 1956-10-27 - Part 1
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Part 1 of Prince Albert tobacco sponsored Grand Ole Opry segment from October 27, 1956. Featuring Grant Turner (announcer), Webb Pierce (host/performer), guest performer Jean Shepard, and regular performers the Old Hickory Singers, Del Wood, the Duke Of Paducah, and Grandpa Jones. The Duke Of Paducah mentions that Minnie Pearl is snowed-in in Calgary, Alberta, Canada. Held at Ryman Auditorium, Nashville, TN.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Webb Pierce; Old Hickory Singers; Jean Shepard; Del Wood; Duke Of Paducah
